project_details:
Other responsibilities include the following:

Appraising agency-produced records against the disposition schedule in order to determine their suitability for inclusion in the park’s resource management records collection;
Archival conservation of many records formats, including paper, photographs, negatives, slides, videocassettes, compact discs, cyanotypes, and electronic files;
Writing detailed, accurate archival descriptions of collections materials which encompass the functions and processes documented within the collection’s series;
Developing and implementing an organizational hierarchy for each collection which reflects the provenance of the collection’s records;
Separating, flattening, rolling, and processing of oversized documents including maps, project schematics, and architectural drawings;
Cataloging park archival collections at project closeout in the agency’s cataloging database, MCMS;
Appropriate documentation and destruction of temporary records beyond the retention date encountered during the course of the processing project

Project Timeline: Full Time (40 hours/week) for a 54-week appointment starting early June 2026
